# UTM Parameters — Master Rule Set

**ALL** social media posts, marketing campaigns, and external links **MUST** include properly formatted UTM parameters. This is non-negotiable.

---

## URL Structure

```
https://www.stonerise.tech/[page]?utm_source=[source]&utm_medium=[medium]&utm_campaign=[campaign]&utm_content=[content]&utm_term=[term]
```

---

## Parameters

### utm_source — WHERE the traffic comes from

**Format:** `[platform]_[account_type]`

| Platform / Account | Value |
|--------------------|-------|
| Michael Loizias LinkedIn | `linkedin_michael` |
| Stelios Ioannou LinkedIn | `linkedin_stelios` |
| StoneRise Company LinkedIn | `linkedin_company` |
| StoneRise Facebook | `facebook_company` |
| StoneRise Instagram | `instagram_company` |
| StoneRise Twitter/X | `twitter_company` |
| Email campaigns | `email` |
| Google Ads | `google_ads` |
| Meta Ads (FB/IG paid) | `meta_ads` |

✅ `utm_source=linkedin_michael`  
❌ `utm_source=linkedin` (missing account type)  
❌ `utm_source=Michael` (wrong format)

---

### utm_medium — HOW the traffic arrives

**Format:** `[type]`

| Traffic Type | Value |
|--------------|-------|
| Unpaid social posts | `organic_social` |
| Paid social ads | `paid_social` |
| Email campaigns | `email` |
| Google PPC | `cpc` |
| Retargeting ads | `retargeting` |
| Partner / referral links | `partnership` |

✅ `utm_medium=organic_social`  
❌ `utm_medium=social` (not specific enough)

---

### utm_campaign — WHAT campaign or initiative

**Format:** `[theme]_[product]`

- **Theme:** Short descriptor of the campaign
- **Product:** `procurement` | `hr` | `commercial` | `hs` | `general`
- **No date** — dates belong in `utm_content` only

✅ `utm_campaign=invoice_ai_procurement`  
✅ `utm_campaign=weekly_post_general`  
❌ `utm_campaign=202602_invoice_ai_procurement` (no date in campaign)  
❌ `utm_campaign=InvoiceAI` (wrong format, missing product)  
❌ `utm_campaign=february` (too vague)

---

### utm_content — WHICH specific post or variant

**Format depends on post type:**

| Post Type | Format | Example |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| Organic social posts | `YYYYMMDD_post[N]` | `20260304_post1` |
| Multiple posts same day | `YYYYMMDD_post[N]` | `20260304_post2` |
| Video ads | `video_[cta]` | `video_demo_cta` |
| Carousel ads | `carousel_[topic]` | `carousel_supplier_mgmt` |
| Static image ads | `static_[type]` | `static_testimonial` |
| Text ads | `text_ad_[variant]` | `text_ad_v1` |

**Date rules:**
- Use ISO 8601 format: `YYYYMMDD` (e.g. March 4, 2026 → `20260304`)
- Post number starts at `post1` and increments for each additional post that day

✅ `utm_content=20260304_post1`  
✅ `utm_content=20260304_post2`  
❌ `utm_content=week1_post1` (old week-based format)  
❌ `utm_content=post1` (no date)  
❌ `utm_content=feb3_post1` (wrong date format)  
❌ `utm_content=03022026_post1` (wrong date order)

---

### utm_term — Paid campaigns only (optional)

**Format:** `[keyword_or_target]`

Only for paid search or paid social with specific targeting.

✅ `utm_term=procurement_software_uk`  
✅ `utm_term=lookalike_demo_bookers`  
— Leave blank for organic posts.

